section.section:
"Supervisory official" means:
The Secretary or Deputy Secretary of State Police;
The chief of police, deputy chief of police, or equivalent official of a law enforcement agency of any political subdivision of the State;
The Attorney General of the State or a Deputy Attorney General;
The State Prosecutor or Deputy State Prosecutor; or
A State's Attorney or Deputy State's Attorney.

"Adverse result" means:
Endangering the life or physical safety of an individual;
Flight from prosecution;
Destruction of or tampering with evidence;
Intimidation of potential witnesses; or
Otherwise seriously jeopardizing an investigation or unduly delaying a trial.
